DOCUMENT();       
loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$p = random(700,900,50);
$diff = random(150,250,50);
$end = $p+$diff;
$r = round( 40000*(($end/$p)**(1/40)-1) )/100;

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 22:
$BR $SPACE $BR
A sum of ${DOLLAR}$p is invested for 10 years and the interest is compounded quarterly.  There is ${DOLLAR}$end in the account at the end of 10 years.
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
What is the nominal annual rate? \{ ans_rule(20) \}$PERCENT
$BR
$BBOLD Round your answer to the nearest 0.01$PERCENT .$EBOLD
$BR
END_TEXT

ANS( num_cmp( $r,tol=>0.005 ) );

$almost1 = round(100000*($end/$p)**(1/40))/100000;
$almost2 = round(($almost1 -1)*100000)/100000;
$almost3 = round($almost2*400000)/100000; 

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 

Let $BITALIC r $EITALIC represent the nominal annual rate.  Since the interest is compounded quarterly, the investment earns \( \frac{r}{4} \) each quarter. So, at the end of the first quarter, the investment is $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( $p \left( 1 + \frac{r}{4} \right) \), $BR
and at the end of the second quarter is $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( $p \left( 1+ \frac{r}{4} \right)^2 \).
$BR
By the end of 10 years (or 40 quarters), it is $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( $p \left( 1+ \frac{r}{4} \right)^{40} \). $BR
But we are told that the value after 10 years is $end, so $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( $end = $p \left( 1+ \frac{r}{4} \right)^{40} \) $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( \frac{$end}{$p} = \left( 1+ \frac{r}{4} \right)^{40} \) $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( \left( \frac{$end}{$p} \right)^{1/40} = 1+ \frac{r}{4} \) $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( $almost1 \approx 1+ \frac{r}{4} \) $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( $almost2 \approx \frac{r}{4} \) $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( r \approx $almost3 \).
$BR
We see that the nominal interest rate is $r${PERCENT}.

END_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.